
Overview of verb grip

The verb grip has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (10) grip -- (hold fast or firmly; "He gripped the steering wheel")
2. (3) grapple, grip -- (to grip or seize, as in a wrestling match; "the two men grappled with each other for several minutes")
3. (2) fascinate, transfix, grip, spellbind -- (to render motionless, as with a fixed stare or by arousing terror or awe; "The snake charmer fascinates the cobra")

